The QLI application process involves four steps:
<ol>
<li>completing a <a href="test1.asp">self-assessment</a> to help you decide if you should apply for membership in the QLI.

<li>securing <a href="test2.asp">written statements</a> from three professional colleagues comparing your personal characteristics and behaviors with those typical of leaders.

<li>preparing <a href="test3.asp">your own statement</a> of self-perceived strengths and weaknesses with respect to the leadership profile and responding to related questions.

<li>attaching a written statement from the appropriate individual in your learning organization indicating that, if selected as a member of the QLI, you will be granted up to five days of leave during the 1998-99 school year to participate in QLI learning activities. If securing such approval is not feasible in your school system by the application deadline, please include a statement from your immediate supervisor or other appropriate administrator that your later request for such leave will be supported by that individual.
